WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:02.020
(Previously)
This is Lynx, my boyfriend.

00:00:02.713 --> 00:00:05.699
I'm sorry for not being
honest with you earlier.

00:00:06.244 --> 00:00:07.930
I understand you all did it

00:00:07.966 --> 00:00:09.403
because you were worried about me.

00:00:09.663 --> 00:00:13.009
All this time, I just
wanted to see you happy.

00:00:13.443 --> 00:00:14.686
And today, I finally did.

00:00:15.148 --> 00:00:17.912
I think you're ready
now to take this power.

00:00:18.286 --> 00:00:20.888
Why do I still only hear "Meow"?

00:00:21.160 --> 00:00:23.378
She said… she just
remembered something important.

00:00:23.421 --> 00:00:27.905
But if I had to pass it
on, it'd have to be… Leo.

00:00:28.010 --> 00:00:29.989
So in the end, I was never
the one you chose, Mom.

00:00:30.013 --> 00:00:33.533
6 MONTHS EARLIER

00:01:06.156 --> 00:01:07.156
Mom,

00:01:09.389 --> 00:01:10.905
when you first opened this café,

00:01:12.614 --> 00:01:13.684
were you able to sleep?

00:01:15.517 --> 00:01:16.525
Of course, you were.

00:01:19.114 --> 00:01:20.511
You were never afraid of anything.

00:01:20.933 --> 00:01:22.621
If there was one thing you were afraid of,

00:01:23.010 --> 00:01:25.090
it would be me
taking over this café from you, right?

00:01:26.808 --> 00:01:28.317
Hey, Granny Juu.

00:01:29.103 --> 00:01:30.103
How did you get in here?

00:01:35.218 --> 00:01:36.218
Hm?

00:01:39.916 --> 00:01:40.917
Your whisker?

00:01:42.787 --> 00:01:43.792
Thank you, Granny.

00:01:45.794 --> 00:01:47.248
Mom sent you to help me, didn't she?

00:01:48.534 --> 00:01:50.312
I'll save it for when I truly need it.

00:01:55.857 --> 00:01:58.913
PRESENT DAY

00:01:59.058 --> 00:02:00.058
Meow.

00:02:08.188 --> 00:02:09.877
Are you worried about me after last night?

00:02:10.140 --> 00:02:14.012
But if I had to pass it on,
it'd have to be…

00:02:19.709 --> 00:02:20.709
Leo.

00:02:22.705 --> 00:02:24.198
That's actually good to know, Granny.

00:02:25.618 --> 00:02:27.404
So I know what Mom really wanted.

00:02:36.383 --> 00:02:37.383
Granny Juu.

00:02:42.995 --> 00:02:44.207
Can you look after Leo for me?

00:03:41.500 --> 00:03:44.000
"Cat For Cash"
(Episode 10)

00:03:46.043 --> 00:03:47.077
Did you get hold of Lynx?

00:03:48.415 --> 00:03:51.487
He hadn't come down yet,
so I went up to his room

00:03:51.734 --> 00:03:53.501
and all I found was
the key and this note.

00:04:00.426 --> 00:04:02.826
LEO, TAKE CARE OF MOM'S CAFÉ FOR ME.

00:04:04.266 --> 00:04:06.504
What's this about? I don't get it.

00:04:08.033 --> 00:04:09.033
Well…

00:04:11.368 --> 00:04:12.397
we just found out

00:04:13.937 --> 00:04:16.087
that Je Meow intended to
hand this café over to you.

00:04:18.545 --> 00:04:19.998
I once joked with Mom

00:04:21.857 --> 00:04:23.558
that if she couldn't run the café anymore,

00:04:24.092 --> 00:04:25.205
I'd take it over.

00:04:26.376 --> 00:04:29.107
Then one day she actually called

00:04:29.407 --> 00:04:30.813
and said she'd give the cafe to me.

00:04:34.028 --> 00:04:35.028
At first,

00:04:36.829 --> 00:04:38.107
I thought she was kidding,

00:04:40.063 --> 00:04:41.128
but it was actually…

00:04:44.178 --> 00:04:45.618
her farewell call.

00:04:58.216 --> 00:04:59.216
Mom…

00:05:00.002 --> 00:05:01.810
Lynx has done such a
good job with this café.

00:05:03.988 --> 00:05:05.683
I don't think I could ever fill his shoes.

00:05:08.512 --> 00:05:13.307
No one is more suited
to run this café than Lynx.

00:05:22.213 --> 00:05:23.213
Well then…

00:05:25.403 --> 00:05:26.603
let's go find Lynx together.

00:05:30.576 --> 00:05:31.616
- Granny Juu!
- Granny Juu!

00:05:38.354 --> 00:05:40.185
It looks like it's what we were afraid of.

00:05:41.340 --> 00:05:42.367
What's wrong with her?

00:05:47.749 --> 00:05:48.761
The other day,

00:05:49.450 --> 00:05:51.115
I took Granny Juu in for a heart checkup.

00:05:52.087 --> 00:05:54.930
They said she wasn't doing well.

00:05:56.588 --> 00:05:58.994
Why didn't you tell us something this important?

00:05:59.155 --> 00:06:00.413
How was I supposed to tell you?

00:06:01.076 --> 00:06:02.996
You two were stressed about
your mom at the time.

00:06:03.826 --> 00:06:04.826
Don't worry.

00:06:05.278 --> 00:06:06.923
Granny Juu is breathing normally again.

00:06:08.591 --> 00:06:11.206
Let's see if her condition will get better.

00:06:11.699 --> 00:06:14.714
(Lynx… where are you, Lynx?)

00:06:43.071 --> 00:06:45.806
How did you know that I'd be here?

00:06:48.551 --> 00:06:50.026
I just hope that our café's cats

00:06:51.564 --> 00:06:53.008
would wander back here again.

00:06:54.864 --> 00:06:57.518
Jiro, let's go home.

00:06:57.905 --> 00:07:00.312
Jiro, come out already.

00:07:00.690 --> 00:07:02.710
That day, I thought I made my mom proud.

00:07:05.952 --> 00:07:08.730
The truth is, she had probably stopped
waiting for me a long time ago.

00:07:09.991 --> 00:07:11.311
Don't be mad at her.

00:07:13.050 --> 00:07:14.103
I just regret it.

00:07:17.811 --> 00:07:19.725
If I had shown up that day
when Mom asked me to,

00:07:22.046 --> 00:07:24.297
we could have sat down together
over Korat fried noodles,

00:07:25.012 --> 00:07:26.076
talked things through,

00:07:29.624 --> 00:07:31.224
and I could have helped her at the café.

00:07:35.892 --> 00:07:37.101
All I can do now is…

00:07:40.122 --> 00:07:42.110
hold on to the blanket
that still has her scent.

00:07:48.505 --> 00:07:49.505
Lynx.

00:07:55.741 --> 00:07:57.105
It's still not too late.

00:08:00.103 --> 00:08:01.624
Granny Juu isn't doing well at all.

00:08:03.450 --> 00:08:04.714
She said she wanted to see you.

00:08:08.740 --> 00:08:09.817
I'm not sure anymore

00:08:11.225 --> 00:08:13.627
if I was the one Mom wanted
to take care of Granny Juu.

00:08:26.384 --> 00:08:27.906
Hello, Leo. What's up?

00:08:34.320 --> 00:08:35.861
DR. KRISTIN CHEEVASOPON
VETERINARIAN

00:08:38.620 --> 00:08:39.620
Lynx,

00:08:40.743 --> 00:08:42.098
Granny Juu is very old now

00:08:42.393 --> 00:08:43.903
and her body is too weak

00:08:44.453 --> 00:08:46.020
so it didn't respond to the medication.

00:08:48.518 --> 00:08:49.518
So I think…

00:08:51.572 --> 00:08:53.116
you should prepare for the worst.

00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:55.812
Hey! Prepare for the worst?

00:08:56.651 --> 00:08:57.707
You're the vet.

00:08:57.924 --> 00:08:59.587
You're supposed to know how to treat her.

00:09:00.467 --> 00:09:03.018
Leo, calm down.

00:09:04.530 --> 00:09:05.716
If medication doesn't work,

00:09:06.032 --> 00:09:07.323
then operate or do something.

00:09:07.451 --> 00:09:08.939
Don't just tell us to prepare to lose her.

00:09:08.963 --> 00:09:10.181
How the hell could we do that?

00:09:12.413 --> 00:09:13.427
You come with me.

00:09:17.774 --> 00:09:19.614
Is there any other way to treat her?

00:09:22.006 --> 00:09:24.100
We could try another medication.

00:09:25.167 --> 00:09:26.713
But no one can guarantee

00:09:26.947 --> 00:09:28.018
it'll work.

00:09:29.392 --> 00:09:31.016
I feel for Granny Juu

00:09:32.016 --> 00:09:33.813
because changing the medication

00:09:36.019 --> 00:09:37.883
will definitely put her
through a lot of pain.

00:09:41.174 --> 00:09:42.198
What did she say?

00:09:48.798 --> 00:09:49.798
She said…

00:09:53.192 --> 00:09:54.313
she wanted to see Je Meow.

00:09:59.642 --> 00:10:02.096
She probably forgot…

00:10:05.901 --> 00:10:07.006
that Je Meow is gone.

00:10:13.894 --> 00:10:14.894
Granny Juu.

00:10:15.700 --> 00:10:17.112
Mom's resting here now.

00:10:22.290 --> 00:10:23.405
She said…

00:10:27.488 --> 00:10:28.513
she misses Je Meow.

00:10:33.422 --> 00:10:34.705
I miss her too.

00:10:39.490 --> 00:10:40.608
She's tired now.

00:10:42.558 --> 00:10:43.558
I think…

00:10:48.087 --> 00:10:49.508
she won't make it back to Bangkok.

00:10:55.526 --> 00:10:56.548
Grandma, Grandpa, hi.

00:10:56.588 --> 00:10:57.588
Hi, dear.

00:10:57.613 --> 00:10:58.613
Hi.

00:10:58.747 --> 00:11:02.008
Hey, Juu. We finally meet.

00:11:04.894 --> 00:11:05.997
Have you eaten?

00:11:06.180 --> 00:11:06.999
Not yet.

00:11:07.062 --> 00:11:09.097
Don't worry. I've got food ready for you.

00:11:09.435 --> 00:11:10.506
Let me help you with that.

00:11:10.607 --> 00:11:11.647
Come on then.

00:11:14.029 --> 00:11:15.052
Grandpa Petch.

00:11:15.190 --> 00:11:16.190
Hm?

00:11:16.736 --> 00:11:17.805
I need your advice.

00:11:18.962 --> 00:11:19.962
What is it?

00:11:20.792 --> 00:11:22.350
I already passed on the power to Lynx.

00:11:23.819 --> 00:11:24.901
But I don't know why

00:11:25.562 --> 00:11:27.206
Lynx still cannot hear cats talking.

00:11:31.925 --> 00:11:34.522
What Lynx has been through is complicated.

00:11:36.014 --> 00:11:37.792
Him living with the cats right now,

00:11:38.384 --> 00:11:39.488
I don't know if it's because he loves them,

00:11:39.512 --> 00:11:41.212
or because he feels guilty about his mom.

00:11:42.392 --> 00:11:43.597
But from what I've seen,

00:11:45.582 --> 00:11:46.984
I think it's because he loves them.

00:11:49.752 --> 00:11:51.398
Do you think Lynx feels the same way?

00:11:59.898 --> 00:12:01.103
Here you are.

00:12:09.216 --> 00:12:10.216
Lynx.

00:12:10.927 --> 00:12:14.700
Tiger told me
that your mom gave the café to Leo.

00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:17.825
It's not surprising.

00:12:20.180 --> 00:12:22.307
If Mom gave what she loved most
to someone,

00:12:24.994 --> 00:12:26.596
she must have loved that person dearly.

00:12:27.988 --> 00:12:30.698
I don't know why she made that decision.

00:12:31.054 --> 00:12:32.398
But what I do know is

00:12:33.327 --> 00:12:36.011
she loved you the most, Lynx.

00:12:40.190 --> 00:12:41.418
Did she tell you that?

00:12:43.269 --> 00:12:45.084
Lynx, I think you know

00:12:45.173 --> 00:12:47.112
that Grandpa can talk to cats.

00:12:48.507 --> 00:12:49.507
Yes.

00:12:50.232 --> 00:12:54.213
I don't have that special
power like he does.

00:12:54.753 --> 00:12:57.996
But when I look into those cats' eyes,

00:12:58.596 --> 00:12:59.911
and see what they are up to,

00:13:00.393 --> 00:13:03.298
I know instantly what they want to tell me.

00:13:07.513 --> 00:13:10.706
I can see what a kind heart you have.

00:13:11.106 --> 00:13:16.906
So I'm sure you were raised
with so much love, dear.

00:13:46.053 --> 00:13:47.186
You can play the piano too?

00:13:50.037 --> 00:13:51.860
I used to learn when I was
in elementary school.

00:13:51.884 --> 00:13:53.197
Every time I played,

00:13:54.236 --> 00:13:55.824
Granny Juu would jump up and bother me.

00:14:06.592 --> 00:14:07.714
How about we play together?

00:14:36.121 --> 00:14:37.121
Granny Juu,

00:14:37.778 --> 00:14:38.897
the song is over,

00:14:40.414 --> 00:14:41.616
why won't you come bother us?

00:14:55.595 --> 00:14:56.730
Let's play it one more time.

00:15:10.653 --> 00:15:12.602
It smells familiar here,
doesn't it, Granny Juu?

00:15:15.410 --> 00:15:16.715
This is Meow's room.

00:15:18.489 --> 00:15:19.489
Hm?

00:15:25.344 --> 00:15:26.400
You're tired now, right?

00:15:27.534 --> 00:15:28.916
Rest easy, Granny Juu.

00:15:29.627 --> 00:15:31.907
We'll take care of Lynx for you.

00:15:34.109 --> 00:15:35.413
Look after Lynx for us too.

00:15:39.868 --> 00:15:41.113
Take care of him.

00:15:48.262 --> 00:15:49.262
Granny Juu.

00:15:50.886 --> 00:15:51.931
Do you remember this?

00:15:53.421 --> 00:15:54.695
You left it for me.

00:15:58.893 --> 00:16:00.051
I'm returning it to you now.

00:16:02.967 --> 00:16:04.515
If you have any wish to make,

00:16:06.671 --> 00:16:07.698
you may do it now.

00:16:10.851 --> 00:16:12.023
Granny Juu said,

00:16:14.715 --> 00:16:16.100
she wished for your happiness.

00:16:22.442 --> 00:16:23.604
My happiness

00:16:24.818 --> 00:16:26.230
is being with you.

00:16:29.760 --> 00:16:31.216
Let's sleep here together.

00:16:49.569 --> 00:16:50.569
Granny Juu.

00:16:57.975 --> 00:16:58.975
Granny Juu.

00:16:59.371 --> 00:17:00.371
Granny…

00:17:19.197 --> 00:17:20.197
Granny Juu.

00:17:43.894 --> 00:17:46.551
FOREVER IN MEMORY

00:17:55.643 --> 00:17:57.992
MAY YOUR SOUL FIND ITS PEACEFUL PLACE.

00:17:59.421 --> 00:18:00.861
ALWAYS IN MY HEART

00:18:07.206 --> 00:18:08.489
Granny Juu.

00:18:09.237 --> 00:18:10.719
I've missed you so much.

00:18:10.744 --> 00:18:12.210
Let me get a good look at you.

00:18:31.238 --> 00:18:32.301
Have you been well?

00:18:36.521 --> 00:18:38.004
We haven't seen each other in so long

00:18:40.316 --> 00:18:41.960
and that's the best greeting you've got?

00:18:44.119 --> 00:18:45.156
Have you eaten?

00:18:45.637 --> 00:18:47.924
No, not that either.

00:18:48.946 --> 00:18:50.101
I've heard that one before.

00:18:53.461 --> 00:18:54.563
I'm sorry, sweetie.

00:18:54.925 --> 00:18:56.013
For what?

00:18:58.247 --> 00:18:59.908
You didn't do anything wrong.

00:19:01.687 --> 00:19:03.015
You made the right call

00:19:04.384 --> 00:19:05.701
not handing everything to me.

00:19:08.413 --> 00:19:10.004
Out of all your kids,

00:19:12.973 --> 00:19:14.684
I'm probably the worst one.

00:19:14.798 --> 00:19:17.203
No, that's not it at all, Lynx.

00:19:17.492 --> 00:19:18.592
I'm sorry, Mom.

00:19:20.010 --> 00:19:21.117
If I had a choice,

00:19:23.703 --> 00:19:25.815
I would have wanted you
to have a better son too.

00:19:28.122 --> 00:19:29.408
If I had a choice,

00:19:31.126 --> 00:19:33.715
I would have wanted my father
to have the son he always wanted.

00:19:37.214 --> 00:19:40.213
I did everything to make him accept me.

00:19:41.381 --> 00:19:43.706
I was a good kid—stayed home,

00:19:44.734 --> 00:19:46.222
did everything he told me to.

00:19:50.099 --> 00:19:52.103
The one thing I was willing
to break with him over

00:19:54.560 --> 00:19:56.408
was deciding to have you.

00:20:01.694 --> 00:20:06.217
If I had chosen the path
my father wanted for me,

00:20:08.195 --> 00:20:09.892
I never would have met you.

00:20:11.458 --> 00:20:15.298
So I wanted you to choose
your own path, just like I did.

00:20:17.384 --> 00:20:18.421
Because I knew

00:20:21.186 --> 00:20:22.804
how proud it would be

00:20:24.183 --> 00:20:26.113
to choose the best thing for yourself.

00:20:34.681 --> 00:20:35.893
If I could choose,

00:20:40.311 --> 00:20:41.811
could I keep running the café?

00:20:44.022 --> 00:20:45.045
Of course, sweetie.

00:20:45.768 --> 00:20:46.808
You can do that

00:20:48.472 --> 00:20:49.954
because you genuinely love the cats.

00:20:59.801 --> 00:21:00.801
Mom.

00:21:03.782 --> 00:21:04.788
Do you love me?

00:21:11.368 --> 00:21:13.214
I made you wake up early,

00:21:14.087 --> 00:21:15.896
and go through the same old routines,

00:21:18.588 --> 00:21:20.521
and put up with me every day.

00:21:21.331 --> 00:21:22.503
No matter how stubborn I was,

00:21:23.184 --> 00:21:25.250
no matter how many times
I turned a deaf ear to you,

00:21:26.097 --> 00:21:27.802
you were still there for me.

00:21:30.451 --> 00:21:32.230
Even though you never said it out loud,

00:21:34.437 --> 00:21:35.797
everything you did for me

00:21:37.348 --> 00:21:38.823
was your way of saying you loved me.

00:21:47.695 --> 00:21:48.695
Then,

00:21:50.441 --> 00:21:51.441
I think…

00:21:53.390 --> 00:21:54.714
I must truly love the cats too.

00:21:57.285 --> 00:21:58.401
I love you, Lynx.

00:22:04.161 --> 00:22:05.161
I love you.

00:22:05.329 --> 00:22:07.106
I love you too.

00:22:11.577 --> 00:22:12.577
I knew.

00:22:14.824 --> 00:22:17.886
I saw everything you did.

00:22:19.634 --> 00:22:22.325
Granny Juu praised you to me every night.

00:22:23.209 --> 00:22:25.102
I'm so proud of you, you know?

00:22:26.644 --> 00:22:29.697
I'm proud to be your mother.

00:22:31.133 --> 00:22:35.087
I'm proud to have raised you
into such a good man.

00:22:37.050 --> 00:22:41.807
And I'm proudest of all
to have been your mother

00:22:42.443 --> 00:22:44.908
until the very last second of my life.

00:22:51.217 --> 00:22:52.958
You're the best.

00:22:54.626 --> 00:22:58.538
It's not too late for
me to say that, right?

00:23:16.489 --> 00:23:17.849
I have to go now.

00:23:19.102 --> 00:23:21.303
We'll see each other again someday.

00:23:21.677 --> 00:23:23.697
No matter where or when,

00:23:24.694 --> 00:23:27.125
I'll be waiting to hold
you like this again.

00:23:30.324 --> 00:23:31.324
Okay?

00:23:40.610 --> 00:23:41.807
See you, sweetie.

00:23:41.995 --> 00:23:42.856
Can you not go?

00:23:42.881 --> 00:23:43.896
See you again.

00:23:43.972 --> 00:23:45.504
Can you not go?

00:25:00.441 --> 00:25:01.441
Lynx.

00:25:06.456 --> 00:25:07.456
Granny Juu.

00:25:11.891 --> 00:25:12.891
Granny Juu.

00:25:13.754 --> 00:25:14.754
(Lynx…)

00:25:17.702 --> 00:25:20.513
(Remember the first day we met?)

00:25:20.912 --> 00:25:24.117
(You promised to take the best care of me.)

00:25:26.164 --> 00:25:29.096
(Thank you for keeping your promise.)

00:25:33.490 --> 00:25:35.602
(See you again.)

00:25:38.226 --> 00:25:39.595
Granny Juu said...

00:25:41.742 --> 00:25:42.835
See you, Granny Juu.

00:25:43.064 --> 00:25:48.402
♪ I told you I love you, love you ♪

00:25:49.162 --> 00:25:54.478
♪ Since the first day I laid eyes on you ♪

00:25:55.014 --> 00:26:00.617
♪ Even though my voice can't be heard ♪

00:26:01.023 --> 00:26:06.682
♪ But someday you'll
understand every word ♪

00:26:07.445 --> 00:26:10.828
♪ Every word ♪

00:26:18.925 --> 00:26:20.817
When I was little,
whenever I played the piano,

00:26:22.499 --> 00:26:25.211
Granny Juu would always jump up
and curl on my lap.

00:26:28.579 --> 00:26:32.512
She must have loved listening to me play.

00:26:35.737 --> 00:26:37.916
And Mom would always praise me

00:26:39.404 --> 00:26:40.508
for playing beautifully,

00:26:43.011 --> 00:26:45.129
even though I always hit the wrong notes.

00:26:46.133 --> 00:26:49.197
I think that was her way of saying
